Three men are expected to appear in court after they allegedly robbed a supermarket at gunpoint in Kakamas. CAPE TOWN - Three men will appear in the Upington Magistrates Court on Wednesday in connection with a business robbery in Kakamas.The men were apprehended shortly after they allegedly robbed a supermarket at gunpoint earlier this week.Police managed to retrieve the vehicle they are believed to have fled in, including the cellphones and a portion of the money they allegedly stole.The police's Mohale Ramatseba says, The cluster commander has commended the police for the good work done and the community which led to the arrest of the three suspects. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)